values:
Robot
You are 85% Rational, 14% Extroverted, 28% Brutal, and 28% Arrogant.
You are the Robot! You are characterized by your rationality. In fact, this is really ALL you are characterized by. Like a cold, heartless machine, you are so logical and unemotional that you scarcely seem human. For instance, you are very humble and don't bother thinking of your own interests, you are very gentle and lack emotion, and you are also very introverted and introspective. You may have noticed that these traits are just as applicable to your laptop as they are to a human being. You are not like the robots they show in the movies. Movie robots are make-believe, because they always get all personable and likeable after being struck by lightning, or they are cold, cruel killing machines. In all reality, though, you are much more boring than all that. Real robots just sit there, doing their stupid jobs, and doing little else. If you get struck by lightning, you won't develop a winning personality and heart of gold. (Robots don't have hearts, silly, and if they did, they would probably be made of steel, not gold.) You also won't be likely to terrorize humanity by becoming an ultra-violent killing machine sent into the past to kill the mother of a child who will lead a rebellion against machines, because that movie was dumb as hell, and because real robots don't kill--they horribly maim at best, and they don't even do that on purpose. Real robots are boringly kind and all too rarely try to kill people. In all my years, my laptop has only attacked me once, and that was only because my brother threw it at me. In short, your personality defect is that you don't really HAVE a personality. You are one of those annoying, super-logical people that never gets upset or flustered. Unless, of course, you short circuit. Or if someone throws a pie at you. Pies sure are delicious.

To put it less negatively:

1. You are more RATIONAL than intuitive.

2. You are more INTROVERTED than extroverted.

3. You are more GENTLE than brutal.

4. You are more HUMBLE than arrogant.

Compatibility:

Your exact opposite is the Class Clown.

Other personalities you would probably get along with are the Hand-Raiser, the Emo Kid, and the Haughty Intellectual.

*

*

If you scored near fifty percent for a certain trait (42%-58%), you could very well go either way. For example, someone with 42% Extroversion is slightly leaning towards being an introvert, but is close enough to being an extrovert to be classified that way as well. Below is a list of the other personality types so that you can determine which other possible categories you may fill if you scored near fifty percent for certain traits.

The other personality types:

The Emo Kid: Intuitive, Introverted, Gentle, Humble.

The Starving Artist: Intuitive, Introverted, Gentle, Arrogant.

The Bitch-Slap: Intuitive, Introverted, Brutal, Humble.

The Brute: Intuitive, Introverted, Brutal, Arrogant.

The Hippie: Intuitive, Extroverted, Gentle, Humble.

The Televangelist: Intuitive, Extroverted, Gentle, Arrogant.

The Schoolyard Bully: Intuitive, Extroverted, Brutal, Humble.

The Class Clown: Intuitive, Extroverted, Brutal, Arrogant.

The Robot: Rational, Introverted, Gentle, Humble.

The Haughty Intellectual: Rational, Introverted, Gentle, Arrogant.

The Spiteful Loner: Rational, Introverted, Brutal, Humble.

The Sociopath: Rational, Introverted, Brutal, Arrogant.

The Hand-Raiser: Rational, Extroverted, Gentle, Humble.

The Braggart: Rational, Extroverted, Gentle, Arrogant.

The Capitalist Pig: Rational, Extroverted, Brutal, Humble.

The Smartass: Rational, Extroverted, Brutal, Arrogant.

Be sure to take my Sublime Philosophical Crap Test if you are interested in taking a slightly more intellectual test that has just as many insane ramblings as this one does!




My test tracked 4 variables How you compared to other people your age and gender:
You scored higher than 99% on Rationality
You scored higher than 99% on Extroversion
You scored higher than 99% on Brutality
You scored higher than 99% on Arrogance

It is interesting the effect of fear on the human psyche, the fear of abandonment of betrayal of sinister dealings in dark places. Do we carry with us the past transgressions and portray all people to be as sick and twisted as the ones we knew before. Do we fear love and its grace its ability to bring forth peace into the hearts of those that have none. Should we question the grace and beauty of protection and forgiveness the awe inspiring compassion of our loved ones? What is this drive for humans to rip themselves apart and throw themselves down on to the gnashing rocks below them?  Why is it that dysfunction is so easy to attain and so difficult to rid ones self of. In time we all find it is us that is the problem and with the strength of those that love us we can free ourselves of that fear.  In life I found my partner and she keeps amazing me everyday. Being loved is the most amazing experience I have ever had. Here is to a life time of learning and a life time with me snuggles.

Lesson of the day: never project your past experience onto a new life you will only return Incorrect assumptions. Conjecture leads to fear, fear leads to sadness, sadness leads to hate, and hate leads to sorrow.

I am amazed how often life throws you a curve ball. you are bopping along feeling like all is well and then some ass comes along and pulls the carpet out from under you and you fall flat on your face and scramble to pick up all the things you dropped from your pockets. I always made this trip to the concrete alone and it always hurt like hell and took me quite some time to pick myself up again. Luckily I always had raw ambition and pride to gather myself back together again with. But for the first time in my life I can say I fell down and hit a pillow of compassion and understanding a pillow that is the epitome of love and a lasting reminder that I am not in this world alone. Sometimes it takes getting the crap beat out of you to really see what love is and how much more then a word it can be. Loving someone when they are down is the greatest test it is the thing that proves it's real I am glad to know the feeling. I am overwhelmed to know someone thinks   I am worth such precious gift. It is something I can never take for granted and something I will always protect and hold dear. I will always carry a great respect and appreciation for someone loving me for me and nothing more taking me for who I am and protecting me when I fall. Perfection is far too insignificant a word to describe me snuggles. Another great thing about falling slowly is, you have a chance to see all the opportunity that awaits you and you end up standing in a better spot for falling so far.

Well today is an extremely long day another twelve hour shift down and two more to do this week. Not sure why the hell I ever made a blog. This is my first venture into the world wide wow and I am unsure if it is where I should be crazily slinging thoughts out at. I never thought that I needed recognition by anyone especially not strangers but I find this activity strangely comforting. Almost as if it is a connection to something some kind of record that I existed. In my line of work everything I do is impermanent not that the servers that this information is stored on aren't but it is disseminated. I guess so if some one some where keeps even a piece of my babble then I guess it is eternal maybe, ok probably not. so where to begin I just started new job working nights in a noc it is pretty good work for pretty good pay but I think it is more about me hiding from the real world and only surrounding myself with what I know, what is safe. Work is a constant they need you so they keep you it isn't like relationships where one person gets tired of you our gets tired of themselves and wants to randomly change. I met a beautiful girl I think she likes me but she is out having fun with other people while I am here hiding in my noc. That seems to be the story of my life had I gotten this job in my last relationship we would probably still be together. But I didn't get it then and now I have it and it is probably going to drive her away because I am only around three days a week. So silly, it is funny I used to read these and think they were funny I even put up some crappy poetry kind of funny really but I don't mind this is really nice. I am sure I will be back tomorrow hopefully tomorrow I will have something a little less inane to say.
